{"cursor":"6399","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\nA 'religious denomination' is a subgroup within a religion that operates under a\ncommon name, tradition, and identity.\n\nThe term describes various Christian denominations (for example, Eastern\nOrthodox, Anglicanism, and the many varieties of Protestantism). The term\nalso describes the four branches of Judaism (Orthodox, Conservative, Reform\nand Reconstructionist), and describes the two main branches of Islam (Sunni\nand Shia).\n\nIn Hinduism, the major deity or philosophical belief identifies a denomination,\nwhich also typically has distinct cultural and religious practices. The major\ndenominations include Shaivism, Shaktism, Vaishnavism and Smartism.\n","linknr":186,"url":"Religious_group","recorded":1362477190,"links":29,"instances":["religion"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Religious denominations|"],"headings":["Formation of denominations","Examples","Multi-denominational","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Prevailing_world_religions_map.png/400px-Prevailing_world_religions_map.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["schism","religion"]],"members":["schism"],"related":["Religion","Christian_denomination","Eastern_Orthodox_Church","Church_of_England","Protestantism","Judaism","Orthodox_Judaism","Conservative_Judaism","Reform_Judaism","Reconstructionist_Judaism","Islam","Sunni_Islam","Shia_Islam","Hinduism","Shaivism","Shaktism","Vaishnavism","Smartism","Theology","Philosophy","Religious_pluralism","Ethics","Spiritual_awakening","Mennonite","Church_of_the_Brethren","M